with a rhyme for "incredible."<i> </i>[laughs]

05:44.302 --> 05:46.846
-I can't do this.
-"Indelible." There it is.

05:46.929 --> 05:48.014
Please, Ben, I'm...

05:50.725 --> 05:54.062
I'm sorry. This was just a huge mistake.

05:56.105 --> 05:56.939
What? Why?

05:57.023 --> 05:59.609
It-- it doesn't matter why.

05:59.692 --> 06:02.612
It matters to me,
'cause I don't think it was a mistake.

06:04.072 --> 06:06.532
I feel like I've waited my whole life
to meet someone like you.

06:07.617 --> 06:11.329
Someone who challenges me
and shows up...

06:12.622 --> 06:16.918
and is this amazing combination
of kind and strong and...

06:18.503 --> 06:19.337
beautiful.

06:20.213 --> 06:21.923
I mean, really beautiful.

06:22.548 --> 06:23.716
Inside and out.

06:24.175 --> 06:25.468
Ben, seriously.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.262
-Oh, God.
-Jen, what--

06:28.346 --> 06:32.225
No, you have no clue who I really am.

06:33.893 --> 06:37.230
And you deserve that person
that you just described.

06:37.897 --> 06:40.900
And I assure you, it is... [scoffs]

06:41.567 --> 06:42.527
...it's not me.

06:45.071 --> 06:46.823
Jen, this is... [laughs]

06:46.906 --> 06:49.283
This is crazy.
What are you talking about? We just...

06:49.909 --> 06:51.661
[stammers] Help me understand.

06:51.744 --> 06:53.871
Is this because it's too soon
after your husband...

06:53.955 --> 06:55.164
-No.
-...or what is it?

06:55.248 --> 06:56.290
No, it's not.

06:56.374 --> 06:59.544
-Okay, can we at least talk about it--
-No, we can't, we fucking can't, okay?

07:01.254 --> 07:02.672
Just, please, just...

07:03.840 --> 07:04.924
Please just go.

07:07.468 --> 07:08.386
Okay.

07:08.469 --> 07:09.470
Okay, please.

07:10.096 --> 07:11.097
[Ben sighs]

07:15.977 --> 07:17.353
You know, I don't know...

07:18.312 --> 07:19.772
what is going on with you, but...

07:21.399 --> 07:24.944
I really hope that someday
you can see yourself the way I see you.

07:26.279 --> 07:27.405
'Cause it's pretty...

07:28.698 --> 07:29.699
it's pretty special.

07:30.158 --> 07:32.368
[door opens and closes]

07:34.996 --> 07:37.373
[sobbing]

07:37.457 --> 07:38.291
Fuck.

07:43.129 --> 07:44.130
Hey, Ben.

07:44.464 --> 07:45.798
Oh. Hey, Charlie.

07:45.882 --> 07:47.842
[chuckles] I was just leaving.

07:49.385 --> 07:50.261
Everything okay?

07:50.470 --> 07:52.430
Yeah, all good. I was just, um...

07:53.222 --> 07:56.100
having a meeting with your mom.
A morning meeting.

07:56.559 --> 07:57.477
Uh-huh.

07:58.186 --> 08:00.354
Uh... it's over.

08:01.898 --> 08:03.107
Hey, uh...

08:04.650 --> 08:06.402
you take good care of yourself, okay?

08:07.528 --> 08:08.362
Okay.

08:08.863 --> 08:09.739
And, um...

08:11.157 --> 08:12.909
you take good care of your mom, too.

08:14.702 --> 08:15.536
Sure.

08:19.290 --> 08:20.583
[door opens]

08:21.751 --> 08:22.877
-[door closes]
-[exhales]

08:25.213 --> 08:28.299
-You're living in Laguna? Fancy. Fancy.
-Mm-hmm.

08:28.382 --> 08:29.217
Who's the fella?

08:29.300 --> 08:30.968
Oh. No, no fella.

08:31.052 --> 08:34.472
I live with my friend Jen
and her two boys, Charlie and Henry.

08:34.555 --> 08:37.308
Oh. You don't have your own family?

08:38.726 --> 08:39.560
No.

08:40.102 --> 08:41.687
But I have them.

08:41.979 --> 08:45.149
Hmm. Well, motherhood's overrated anyway.

08:48.528 --> 08:49.654
Two minutes.

08:49.737 --> 08:52.615
Oh, Frankie,
can't I just get a little bit more?

08:52.698 --> 08:56.077
I'm catching up with my daughter.
Isn't she beautiful?

08:56.160 --> 08:57.078
[laughs]

08:57.161 --> 08:58.621
[Frankie] I see the resemblance.

08:59.997 --> 09:01.666
You can have five minutes, just this once.

09:01.749 --> 09:05.253
Thanks.
Don't think I didn't notice that haircut.

09:09.257 --> 09:11.217
-I don't know how you do it.
-Mnh-mnh.

09:11.300 --> 09:13.052
And still making friends
everywhere you go.

09:13.135 --> 09:15.012
Mmm. You need 'em in this place.

09:17.431 --> 09:18.808
How'd you end up back here?

09:19.100 --> 09:20.768
I can't really talk about it.

09:21.811 --> 09:23.062
But it's the system.

09:23.604 --> 09:27.733
Once you go in, they make it almost
impossible for you not to come back.

09:31.445 --> 09:32.280
Right.

09:36.284 --> 09:37.702
I'm sorry, Mom.

09:39.370 --> 09:40.246
Look...

09:40.705 --> 09:41.622
you were a kid.

09:43.040 --> 09:44.584
They shouldn't have let you testify.

09:44.667 --> 09:46.335
I think about it all the time.

09:47.169 --> 09:48.045
I just...

09:50.089 --> 09:51.465
I had to tell the truth.

09:53.009 --> 09:53.843
Yeah.

09:54.885 --> 09:56.137
You didn't know better.

10:00.099 --> 10:01.392
Look, that's in the past.

10:01.475 --> 10:03.185
Let's live for the future.

10:04.812 --> 10:05.646
All right.

10:08.190 --> 10:10.109
I'd really like to see you more, Mom.

10:10.192 --> 10:12.445
Oh, baby, I'd like that too.

10:13.404 --> 10:16.449
Rumor has it,
I have a parole hearing coming up.

10:17.408 --> 10:19.452
Maybe I'll get out sooner than later.

10:19.535 --> 10:20.369
Really?

10:21.037 --> 10:24.832
Especially if I have a lawyer this time
who didn't get his degree at Costco.

10:24.915 --> 10:25.791
[laughs]

10:26.208 --> 10:29.003
-But good attorneys don't come cheap.
-[Judy] No.

10:31.589 --> 10:34.175
God, I would love to help you, Mom,
but I don't have any money.

10:34.258 --> 10:35.593
[stammers] Oh, no, no, look,

10:36.385 --> 10:38.763
if you can't show up for me like that,
you can't.

10:44.769 --> 10:45.936
Well, maybe I can try.

10:47.396 --> 10:48.606
That would mean a lot.

10:53.986 --> 10:54.820
[Jen] Morning.

10:55.738 --> 10:57.031
-[Henry] Hey, Mom.
-Hello.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.492
So I saw Ben
coming down the stairs earlier.

11:00.284 --> 11:01.118
Ben was here?

11:01.327 --> 11:04.914
Uh, yeah, he was here for just a second
to talk about some real estate stuff.

11:05.456 --> 11:06.290
In your bedroom?

11:06.374 --> 11:07.208
Yes.

11:09.752 --> 11:11.379
Well, he seemed upset when he left.

11:12.046 --> 11:12.880
He did?

11:14.090 --> 11:14.924
Yeah.

11:15.216 --> 11:16.175
Oh, shut up!

11:16.258 --> 11:17.510
I didn't say anything.

11:17.593 --> 11:19.595
No, honey, I'm sorry.
It's not you, it's...

11:19.720 --> 11:23.307
[huffs] The city council
denied my stop sign petition.

11:23.391 --> 11:24.558
-Seriously?
-Why?

11:24.642 --> 11:25.685
I don't know, it doesn't say.

11:25.768 --> 11:29.063
It's just an impersonal rejection
from some faceless assholes.

11:29.313 --> 11:31.190
So that's it?
We did all that work for nothing?

11:33.943 --> 11:35.528
No. That's not it.

11:37.780 --> 11:40.616
-[Henry] Where are you going?
-To make them tell me to my face.

11:40.991 --> 11:42.743
-Can I come with you?
-Uh, no, you may not.

11:42.827 --> 11:45.329
You are gonna finish your breakfast,
and when you're done eating,

11:45.413 --> 11:47.957
you're gonna take your bowl
to the dishwasher for once in your life.

11:48.040 --> 11:50.084
I'm on your side. Why are you mad at me?

11:50.167 --> 11:52.253
[Jen] I'm not, I'm just covering my bases.

11:52.336 --> 11:53.337
[Charlie muttering]

12:02.763 --> 12:04.724
[woman] I mean, I've done the research,

12:04.890 --> 12:07.226
and the numbers are very compelling.

12:08.310 --> 12:10.563
I'm just very passionate about this.

12:11.605 --> 12:14.066
So I think, in terms of medians...

12:16.235 --> 12:17.111
we shouldn't.

12:23.117 --> 12:24.410
Hi. Jen Harding,

12:24.744 --> 12:28.622
real estate agent, mom,
and I am here to say no.

12:29.707 --> 12:30.541
To medians?

12:30.624 --> 12:31.876
No, to you.

12:32.001 --> 12:33.085
I beg your pardon.

12:33.169 --> 12:35.171
I submitted a proposal for a stop sign

12:35.254 --> 12:37.506
that was just rejected by this council,

12:37.590 --> 12:39.759
so I am here to reject your rejection.

12:39.842 --> 12:42.136
Well, I'm sorry,
but this is the median hearing.

12:42.219 --> 12:44.013
Well, now we're gonna
talk about stop signs.

12:44.096 --> 12:46.515
Well, unfortunately,
that request was denied

12:46.974 --> 12:49.351
because stop signs slow down traffic.

12:49.894 --> 12:51.604
Uh, that's the point.

12:51.687 --> 12:54.857
After review, the board actually felt
that it could do more harm than good.

12:54.940 --> 12:55.775
I'm sorry,

12:56.275 --> 12:57.735
who's a stop sign gonna harm?

12:58.277 --> 13:01.280
Except for some asshole who bought a Lambo

13:01.363 --> 13:03.699
-to compensate for his micro dick?
-[crowd murmuring]

13:03.783 --> 13:05.701
Miss, we really don't need
that kind of language.

13:05.785 --> 13:06.619
Okay.... [groans]

13:06.702 --> 13:08.746
Please don't call me "miss."
That is annoying.

13:08.871 --> 13:10.372
I'm a full-grown fucking woman,

13:11.040 --> 13:13.876
and I have a teenage son
who's about to get his driver's license,

13:13.959 --> 13:15.336
and I am trying to protect him

13:16.212 --> 13:18.297
and make this neighborhood safer for him

13:18.380 --> 13:19.465
and for all of you.

13:19.548 --> 13:20.883
You know, Mrs. Harding,

13:20.966 --> 13:24.094
I find it interesting
that you're so concerned

13:24.178 --> 13:26.263
about keeping your neighbors safe.

13:26.764 --> 13:27.807
I'm sorry, do I know you?

13:27.890 --> 13:30.726
Yeah, we met. The name's Andrew.

13:31.519 --> 13:32.436
Andrew Peters.

13:33.896 --> 13:37.691
You might remember me from when you
offered me a free estimate on my house

13:37.775 --> 13:39.109
and then assaulted me.

13:39.193 --> 13:41.445
-Get the fuck off me!
-[grunts, shouts]

13:41.612 --> 13:43.113
No means motherfucking no.

13:43.197 --> 13:44.073
You bitch!

13:44.406 --> 13:45.825
You almost broke my nose.

13:47.326 --> 13:48.536
I should have hit you harder.

13:49.119 --> 13:49.954
Excuse me?

13:50.538 --> 13:52.289
Well, you may remember

13:52.373 --> 13:54.375
that the reason I tried to break your nose

13:54.458 --> 13:56.627
is 'cause you were trying
to force yourself on me

13:56.710 --> 13:58.963
after I repeatedly said no.

13:59.797 --> 14:04.635
And I said no to you,
not just because you are fucking gross...

14:05.845 --> 14:07.513
but because I had just lost my husband,

14:08.055 --> 14:09.723
and the last thing that I needed

14:09.807 --> 14:13.269
was to be molested
by some smug, horny prick.

14:13.352 --> 14:14.478
That's not what happened.

14:14.562 --> 14:16.397
Well, could have used
a stop sign that day, huh?

14:16.480 --> 14:17.565
-[woman] Yeah.
-[crowd murmuring]

14:21.777 --> 14:24.405
And if there had been a stop sign

14:25.322 --> 14:27.408
on the road where my husband was killed...

14:28.200 --> 14:29.660
he might be alive today.

14:30.619 --> 14:32.872
And my boys would still have their father.

14:34.415 --> 14:36.667
And our world wouldn't have fallen apart.

14:38.294 --> 14:41.589
[man] Mrs. Harding, though I'm sorry
to hear about your husband's death,

14:41.672 --> 14:44.258
we don't know that a stop sign
could have saved him.

14:46.510 --> 14:47.970
No, we don't.

14:49.096 --> 14:50.598
But it's one stop sign.

14:52.808 --> 14:55.769
And if there is a chance
of saving someone else

14:55.853 --> 14:59.273
from having to feel how I feel every day
of my life,

14:59.356 --> 15:01.066
then trust me, it is worth it.

15:01.859 --> 15:04.194
Because I wouldn't wish this on anyone.

15:07.656 --> 15:08.490
Even you.

15:09.241 --> 15:11.243
[applause beginning]

15:23.672 --> 15:24.632
Hi.

15:25.049 --> 15:25.883
Miss Hale.

15:25.966 --> 15:28.177
-I think you can call me Judy by now.
-I don't.

15:28.260 --> 15:29.887
Okay. I brought you something.

15:35.184 --> 15:36.018
It's Flo.

15:36.393 --> 15:38.646
I heard she's feeling better.
I mean, not from Michelle,

15:38.729 --> 15:40.814
because she won't return my texts,
which is really hurtful,

15:40.898 --> 15:41.732
-but I--
-Seriously?

15:41.815 --> 15:42.733
Sorry.

15:42.816 --> 15:44.276
Thank you for this.

15:44.360 --> 15:45.361
You're welcome.

15:46.487 --> 15:48.739
I was also hoping that
maybe you could do me a favor.

15:48.822 --> 15:51.033
You think you're in a position
to ask me for favors?

15:51.116 --> 15:53.869
Probably not, but it's about my paintings.
I'm just looking for them.

15:53.953 --> 15:57.331
There's a whole collection of little girls
with holes in their hearts.

15:57.706 --> 15:59.375
-Okay.
-I know it sounds weird,

15:59.458 --> 16:02.461
but they're worth something, and last time
I saw them was at Steve's gallery.

16:02.544 --> 16:04.463
Stop talking.
I have something to show you. Prager!

16:07.007 --> 16:08.050
[Nick] Hello, Judy.

16:08.592 --> 16:11.679
Hey, Nick.
Good to see you back in uniform.

16:12.054 --> 16:13.055
Uh, is it?

16:17.101 --> 16:20.270
[Perez] Can you do me a favor and explain
to me what's happening in these photos?

16:22.231 --> 16:23.524
That is not what it looks like.

16:23.607 --> 16:26.068
Oh, that's not Charlie Harding
with Steve Wood's car?

16:27.027 --> 16:30.030
Charlie has nothing to do
with anything about Steve.

16:30.864 --> 16:31.782
Okay, then...

16:31.865 --> 16:34.368
help us understand why
there's also CCTV footage

16:34.451 --> 16:36.620
of Charlie driving Steve's car
the night it was burned.

16:38.330 --> 16:39.206
Well, I--

16:39.289 --> 16:41.875
Look, our boss is itching for us
to make an arrest in this case.

16:41.959 --> 16:43.585
And he thinks we should be looking at you.

16:44.670 --> 16:45.587
-He does?
-[Perez] He does.

16:45.671 --> 16:47.131
But it's a little hard not
to look at this.

16:47.214 --> 16:48.924
It's our only actual lead.

16:50.801 --> 16:51.802
Yeah.

16:51.885 --> 16:53.262
Well, those are just a few pictures.

16:53.345 --> 16:54.763
[Nick] They don't tell a very good story.

16:54.847 --> 16:57.057
We know Charlie's angry
about his father's death.

16:57.141 --> 16:58.976
And we know he's had access to a gun.

16:59.059 --> 17:01.478
[Perez] The question is whether
he was angry enough to use it, which,

17:01.562 --> 17:04.148
-obviously, we're gonna have to ask him.
-He didn't. That's not what happened.

17:06.608 --> 17:07.526
Then what did?

17:10.988 --> 17:13.240
Look, Charlie's the one
who needs a favor now,

17:13.323 --> 17:15.909
so if you got a better story,
you need to tell us quickly.

17:25.252 --> 17:26.837
Char, Hen!

17:27.463 --> 17:28.797
Mama made dinner!

17:29.631 --> 17:31.425
Sort of a once-in-a-lifetime thing here.

17:32.176 --> 17:35.304
Probably gonna taste like shit,
but that's my love just tasting like shit.

17:36.722 --> 17:37.556
Hello!

17:40.059 --> 17:41.602
Hey, Boop. Dinner's ready.

17:42.519 --> 17:43.520
I'm not hungry.

17:43.604 --> 17:45.606
Hmm? No? What's going on? Are you okay?

17:46.815 --> 17:49.109
-I got into a fight with Shandy.
-Oh.

17:49.318 --> 17:50.986
I don't want to be her friend anymore.

17:51.320 --> 17:52.154
Why?

17:52.696 --> 17:54.239
You guys can't talk it out?

17:54.323 --> 17:56.950
I mean, Shandy, you know, seems like...

17:57.701 --> 17:58.994
very reasonable.

18:00.287 --> 18:01.371
She killed my bird.

18:03.624 --> 18:06.668
-She did?
-I know you told her to lie about it.

18:08.879 --> 18:09.838
Oh.

18:10.589 --> 18:11.548
Why did you do that?

18:12.382 --> 18:13.675
[stammers] I don't...

18:14.301 --> 18:15.385
I don't know, honey.

18:16.178 --> 18:17.012
I'm sorry.

18:17.096 --> 18:19.389
I just-- I knew how upset you were
about the bird,

18:19.473 --> 18:22.851
and I just didn't want you
to feel any worse.

18:22.935 --> 18:24.186
But I do feel worse.

18:24.394 --> 18:27.022
You're my mom,
and you fucking lied to me.

18:28.232 --> 18:29.525
Yeah, um...

18:31.110 --> 18:33.862
Look, I-- I made a mistake, okay?

18:35.531 --> 18:37.574
Moms make mistakes sometimes.

18:38.617 --> 18:39.952
I'm really sorry, honey.

18:40.410 --> 18:42.329
What can I do to make it up to you?

18:42.412 --> 18:43.872
Do you want to go to the arcade?

18:45.624 --> 18:46.667
No.

18:46.750 --> 18:50.921
But maybe when Judy gets home,
she can come up to my room?

18:53.882 --> 18:54.758
Okay.

19:00.597 --> 19:01.974
You have your bird, huh?

19:02.599 --> 19:03.600
Yeah, but...

19:04.434 --> 19:06.562
somehow its-- its tail broke.

19:08.689 --> 19:09.523
Yeah.

19:12.860 --> 19:14.778
All right, well, I love you. [kisses]

19:19.616 --> 19:20.534
Okay.

19:24.413 --> 19:26.957
-Hey, we need to fucking talk.
-What? Oh, God, what now?

19:27.040 --> 19:29.835
I'm not Henry. You don't have to hide shit
from me. You don't have to lie.

19:29.918 --> 19:31.420
Okay, what are you talking about, Charlie?

19:31.503 --> 19:32.337
Everything.

19:33.130 --> 19:36.008
Ben, Steve.
I know you're the one who burned his car.

19:37.050 --> 19:39.136
You had a fucking gas can in your hand.

19:39.261 --> 19:41.180
Look, you don't know
what you're talking about.

19:41.305 --> 19:43.515
Okay? It's none of your fucking business.

19:43.599 --> 19:45.100
It is! It is my business.

19:45.601 --> 19:48.145
You're my mother. Aren't we supposed
to look out for each other?

19:48.228 --> 19:50.189
Yeah. Yeah, we are.

19:50.856 --> 19:53.025
So you need to drop it, okay?

19:53.108 --> 19:54.318
-What--
-Trust me.

19:55.027 --> 19:55.861
Why can't you tell me

19:55.944 --> 19:57.571
-what the fuck is going on?
-Because I can't.

19:57.654 --> 19:58.780
-Why not?
-Because.

19:58.864 --> 19:59.865
Why?

20:00.824 --> 20:03.202
[shuddering] Because I'm scared.

20:05.162 --> 20:07.706
[sighs] Steve Wood...

20:08.707 --> 20:12.502
was involved
with some very dangerous people, okay?

20:13.795 --> 20:16.006
So you, please,

20:16.673 --> 20:19.718
don't say another word
about this ever again.

20:19.801 --> 20:20.844
Do you understand me? 

20:20.928 --> 20:21.762
Yeah.

20:22.221 --> 20:25.766
Not another word, Charlie.

20:27.851 --> 20:28.685
Okay.

20:32.064 --> 20:33.106
What? What is that?

20:35.609 --> 20:36.443
Nothing.

20:44.910 --> 20:46.620
[Nick]
<i>You don't really think the kid did it.</i>

20:46.703 --> 20:48.914
I'm just going off the evidence.
It's all we have.

20:50.624 --> 20:53.627
-Did you take a look at what I gave you?
-I did.

20:53.919 --> 20:55.712
But we need more.
A couple of photos of a guy

20:55.796 --> 20:57.547
walking into an art gallery
doesn't prove much.

20:57.631 --> 20:59.675
Neither does a couple photos
of the kid in the car.

21:00.509 --> 21:02.219
-[clears throat]
-[telephone rings]

21:02.302 --> 21:05.305
Prager, my man, those phones
aren't gonna answer themselves.

21:07.307 --> 21:08.141
So, um...

21:08.934 --> 21:11.186
what did Judy Hale have to say
for herself?

21:11.270 --> 21:12.562
She's not talking yet.

21:12.646 --> 21:14.398
Did you dangle the kid?

21:14.481 --> 21:16.275
I... did.

21:16.942 --> 21:18.527
-Good girl.
-I'm not your girl.

21:18.986 --> 21:19.820
Sorry.

21:20.404 --> 21:23.282
I thought that would be a compliment
for a woman your age.

21:24.908 --> 21:25.742
Bitch.

21:35.627 --> 21:38.171
-[door opens and closes]
-[sighs]

21:39.631 --> 21:40.465
Hey.

21:42.342 --> 21:44.428
I need to see you in the garage, please.
Now.

21:46.263 --> 21:49.266
Really? Just-- fuck. Okay.

21:50.642 --> 21:51.643
[Jen] Hey, hey.

21:53.145 --> 21:54.313
What's going on?

21:56.273 --> 21:58.150
What's going on?
Judy, just tell me what's going on.

21:59.192 --> 22:01.945
The police have pictures
of Charlie driving Steve's car,

22:02.029 --> 22:03.030
the ones that Parker took.

22:03.572 --> 22:04.406
Oh, my God.

22:04.656 --> 22:06.533
They also have him on CCTV...

22:07.784 --> 22:10.203
-driving the car the night it was burned.
-Oh, my God.

22:10.370 --> 22:11.913
They think he did it, Jen.

22:11.997 --> 22:14.124
No, no, no, no.

22:14.207 --> 22:15.834
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

22:15.917 --> 22:16.918
What am I gonna do?

22:17.294 --> 22:18.837
-What am I gonna do, Judy?
-Nothing.

22:18.920 --> 22:19.921
Oh, my God.

22:20.005 --> 22:21.381
-Listen to me. Nothing.
-What?

22:21.757 --> 22:23.050
I'm gonna take the blame.

22:24.009 --> 22:25.886
What? No, no, you're not.

22:25.969 --> 22:27.846
I'm not asking you. I'm telling you.

22:27.929 --> 22:30.515
-Oh, fuck, no!
-You are going to let me do this.

22:30.599 --> 22:31.433
I need to do this.

22:31.516 --> 22:32.809
Oh, my God, Judy.

22:32.893 --> 22:33.894
-No.
-Yes.

22:34.186 --> 22:35.228
Listen to me.

22:36.897 --> 22:38.315
The night that Steve died...

22:40.484 --> 22:41.943
I was gonna kill myself.

22:42.527 --> 22:43.403
What?

22:43.487 --> 22:44.988
But then you called me,

22:45.697 --> 22:46.865
and you saved me.

22:48.075 --> 22:48.909
Oh, Judy.

22:48.992 --> 22:52.245
And maybe you saved me for a reason,
so that I can do this for you now.

22:52.913 --> 22:53.997
You have a family.

22:54.414 --> 22:55.332
You have a life.

22:55.874 --> 22:57.667
Please let me do this for you, Jen.

22:57.751 --> 22:59.628
I'm responsible for all of this.

22:59.711 --> 23:01.797
If it wasn't for me,
none of this would have happened.

23:01.880 --> 23:04.549
You're not responsible for Steve's death.

23:04.716 --> 23:05.550
I am.

23:05.634 --> 23:07.135
-Yes, I am.
-No, you're not.

23:07.219 --> 23:09.596
He came here looking for me,
and then he attacked you.

23:09.679 --> 23:10.514
No.

23:10.597 --> 23:13.392
-Yes, it was self-defense, Jen.
-No, it wasn't.

23:13.475 --> 23:14.309
Yes, it was.

23:14.393 --> 23:15.685
No, it wasn't, Judy.

23:16.436 --> 23:17.604
What are you talking about?

23:19.564 --> 23:20.899
He was walking away.

23:23.985 --> 23:25.487
And he didn't attack me, okay?

23:26.321 --> 23:27.239
I attacked him.

23:31.284 --> 23:33.620
-No, you said that he was strangling you.
-No, I...

23:33.703 --> 23:34.538
I lied.

23:34.913 --> 23:35.747
You what?

23:35.831 --> 23:36.665
I lied.

23:37.290 --> 23:38.125
I'm sorry.

23:39.126 --> 23:42.379
No, I don't understand why you--
why would you do that?

23:43.046 --> 23:44.840
Why-- why would you kill him?

23:46.091 --> 23:47.801
[Steve]
<i>He was looking for a way out, honey.</i>

23:48.677 --> 23:51.680
-What?
-Ted. He jumped in front of our car.

23:51.763 --> 23:52.931
[glass shatters]

23:53.014 --> 23:55.892
-No.
-Oh, yeah, he wanted to get hit.

23:55.976 --> 23:56.852
[police siren wails]

23:56.935 --> 23:58.728
Fuck you.

23:58.812 --> 24:00.272
You know what? I don't fucking blame him,

24:00.355 --> 24:03.191
because if I was married to you,
I'd want to put a fucking gun to my head.

24:03.275 --> 24:06.069
I'd want to kill myself, too,
you miserable cunt!

24:08.488 --> 24:09.531
-[blow lands]
-[Jen grunts]

24:11.658 --> 24:14.202
'Cause he was saying
some really bad things, okay?

24:14.703 --> 24:17.080
And I got really angry and I...

24:17.581 --> 24:18.457
I just lost it.

24:21.042 --> 24:22.210
What did he say to you?

24:22.294 --> 24:23.962
I can't-- it doesn't fucking matter.

24:24.045 --> 24:25.464
-Yes, it does.
-No.

24:25.964 --> 24:27.549
-What did he say to you?
-No, it doesn't--

24:27.632 --> 24:29.759
It obviously matters,
'cause you fucking killed him.

24:29.843 --> 24:31.094
What the fuck did he say to you?

24:31.178 --> 24:33.346
He said that Ted jumped
in front of that car!

24:34.890 --> 24:37.809
Okay? He said that
he wanted to die because of me.

24:43.648 --> 24:45.817
-You know that's not true, right?
-It's true.

24:45.901 --> 24:46.860
No, it's not.

24:47.611 --> 24:49.654
None of that is true.
That's just what Steve did.

24:49.738 --> 24:50.989
He wanted to hurt you.

24:51.615 --> 24:53.450
-That's how he was.
-[sobbing]

24:53.700 --> 24:55.368
No, he was right, Judy.

24:56.161 --> 24:58.413
I'm-- I'm a piece of shit.

24:59.664 --> 25:01.500
I'm a fucking piece of shit.

25:02.584 --> 25:05.462
[shuddering] Ted fucking hated me,

25:05.545 --> 25:08.340
my kids fucking hate me,
I fucking hate me.

25:08.423 --> 25:10.717
Everybody just fucking hates me.

25:11.176 --> 25:12.802
I don't hate you.

25:13.345 --> 25:14.804
-I could never hate you--
-Oh, God,

25:14.888 --> 25:18.433
that's because you love anyone who just
gives you a morsel of fucking attention,

25:18.517 --> 25:19.768
even if it's abusive.

25:19.851 --> 25:21.853
It's like you get off on it or something.

25:21.978 --> 25:25.982
It's why you loved Steve and why you love
your shitty, fucking asshole mother!

25:26.566 --> 25:28.485
You'll just stick around for anybody.

25:37.619 --> 25:39.788
-[door slams shut]
-Shit. [sobs]

25:41.373 --> 25:42.457
Judy, wait.

25:42.541 --> 25:44.125
Stop, stop, stop, stop, please.

25:44.292 --> 25:46.336
Look, I didn't mean it, okay?
I didn't mean that.

25:46.419 --> 25:47.546
No, listen to me. Listen to me.

25:47.629 --> 25:50.257
Listen to me, stop.
I am so sorry. Okay, listen. Listen.

25:50.340 --> 25:53.843
It's okay to be angry. You should be
fucking irate right now. I deserve that.

25:53.927 --> 25:55.178
-Don't.
-You should punch me in the face.

25:55.262 --> 25:56.429
-Come on, please.
-No.

25:56.513 --> 25:57.931
-Come on, hit me, please.
-No.

25:58.014 --> 25:59.391
No, wait, just punch me in the face.

26:00.141 --> 26:01.351
I'm not like you.

26:03.144 --> 26:04.354
No, don't, please.

26:04.688 --> 26:07.232
Don't go. Don't go. Please, just hit me!

26:07.649 --> 26:08.567
Move!

26:08.650 --> 26:09.734
-Please!
-I need you to move.

26:09.818 --> 26:11.111
-Out of the way.
-Just hit me!

26:11.194 --> 26:12.404
-Get out of the way!
-No!

26:12.487 --> 26:14.573
-Move, Jen!
-Just fucking run me over!

26:14.656 --> 26:16.449
-Stop it!
-Hit me!

26:16.533 --> 26:19.286
[screaming] Stop!

26:19.494 --> 26:22.581
Stop it! [panting]

26:22.664 --> 26:26.668
Just fucking stop it! [crying]

26:29.254 --> 26:31.089
Just stop it.

26:31.506 --> 26:33.341
Just stop it.

26:33.425 --> 26:35.594
[sobbing]

26:37.053 --> 26:37.929
Judy.

26:42.934 --> 26:43.768
Judy.

26:43.935 --> 26:46.062
Come here. Come here. Come here.

26:46.146 --> 26:48.148
Come here. Come here. Come here.

26:48.231 --> 26:50.233
Okay. It's okay.

26:51.860 --> 26:52.694
It's okay.

26:53.153 --> 26:55.196
[sobbing] It's not okay.

26:55.572 --> 26:57.198
It's not okay.

26:58.199 --> 26:59.451
I know.

27:01.202 --> 27:03.204
[sobbing continuing]

27:04.748 --> 27:07.709
["It's Just a Matter of Time"
by Brook Benton playing]

27:16.051 --> 27:18.219
<i>♪ Some day ♪</i>

27:19.721 --> 27:22.265
<i>♪ Some way ♪</i>

27:22.807 --> 27:25.435
<i>♪ You'll realize ♪</i>

27:25.518 --> 27:30.106
<i>♪ That you've been blind ♪</i>

27:31.483 --> 27:33.485
<i>♪ Yes, darling ♪</i>

27:34.194 --> 27:37.947
<i>♪ You're going to need me again ♪</i>

27:38.782 --> 27:43.453
<i>♪ It's just a matter of time ♪</i>

27:44.454 --> 27:50.043
<i>♪ Go on, go on ♪</i>

27:51.753 --> 27:57.926
<i>♪ Until you reach the end of the line ♪</i>

27:58.968 --> 28:01.763
<i>♪ But I know ♪</i>

28:02.138 --> 28:05.308
<i>♪ You'll pass my way again ♪</i>

28:07.644 --> 28:12.065
<i>♪ It's just a matter of time ♪</i>

28:13.316 --> 28:16.903
<i>♪ After I gave you ♪</i>

28:17.529 --> 28:21.032
<i>♪ Everything I had ♪</i>

28:22.409 --> 28:26.913
<i>♪ You laughed and called me a clown ♪</i>

28:27.872 --> 28:33.461
<i>♪ Remember in your search for fortune ♪</i>

28:33.545 --> 28:35.547
<i>♪ And fame ♪</i>

28:35.630 --> 28:41.386
<i>♪ What goes up must come down ♪</i>

28:41.469 --> 28:45.765
<i>♪ I... I know ♪</i>

28:46.891 --> 28:49.519
<i>♪ I know ♪</i>

28:50.562 --> 28:56.651
<i>♪ That one day you'll wake up and find ♪</i>

28:57.902 --> 29:00.488
<i>♪ That my love ♪</i>

29:01.573 --> 29:05.410
<i>♪ Was a true love ♪</i>

29:06.703 --> 29:08.621
<i>♪ It's just a matter ♪</i>

29:08.747 --> 29:09.581
Jen?

29:09.831 --> 29:13.668
<i>♪ Of time ♪</i>

29:13.752 --> 29:15.044
[knock on door]

29:19.591 --> 29:20.425
Mrs. Harding.

29:21.509 --> 29:22.761
What are you doing here?

29:24.387 --> 29:25.930
There's something I have to confess.

29:27.390 --> 29:29.392
[theme music playing]

31:06.990 --> 31:08.408
[meows]
